":"Haversham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): metonymic occupational name for a maker of habergeons, from Middle English, Old French <i>haubergeon</i>. The habergeon was a medieval sleeveless jacket of mail or scale armor, which was also worn for penance.","History: Born in Beverley, Yorkshire, England, James Habersham emigrated to the infant colony of Georgia in 1738 with his friend George Whitefield. Together they established what is believed to be America's first orphanage. Habersham was married in Bethesda, GA, in 1740 and had three surviving sons, all of whom were educated at Princeton and became ardent patriots."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Nicholas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the post-classical Greek personal name <i>Nikolaos</i>, derived from <i>nikē</i> ‘victory’ + <i>laos</i> ‘people’. The spelling with <i>-ch-</i> first occurred as early as the 12th century, and became firmly established at the time of the Reformation, although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicholas de Haversham II was born in 1240, in Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Nicholas I Haversham, was 21 and his mother, Emma Bois, was 18. He married Mrs. Joan Haversham in 1273, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1274, in his hometown, at the age of 34."},"et":{"1240–1274":"1240–1274","1244–1276":"1244–1276","1260–1240":"1260–1240","1273–1329":"1273–1329","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1222–Female":"1222–Surnud","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1244":"1244","1276":"1276","1220":"1220","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1329":"1329","Haversham, Buckinghamshire,  England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"1240–1274":"1240–1274","1244–1276":"1244–1276","1260–1240":"1260–1240","1273–1329":"1273–1329","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1222–Female":"1222–Kuollut","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1244":"1244","1276":"1276","1220":"1220","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1329":"1329","Haversham, Buckinghamshire,  England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England"},"fr":{"1240–1274":"1240–1274","1244–1276":"1244–1276","1260–1240":"1260–1240","1273–1329":"1273–1329","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1222–Female":"1222–Décédée","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1244":"1244","1276":"1276","1220":"1220","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1329":"1329","Haversham, Buckinghamshire,  England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Nicholas de Haversham II est né en 1240, à Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Nicholas I Haversham, avait 21 ans et sa mère, Emma Bois, avait 18 ans. Il a épousé Mrs. Joan Haversham en 1273, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1274, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 34 ans."},"de":{"1240–1274":"1240–1274","1244–1276":"1244–1276","1260–1240":"1260–1240","1273–1329":"1273–1329","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1222–Female":"1222–Verstorben","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1244":"1244","1276":"1276","1220":"1220","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1329":"1329","Haversham, Buckinghamshire,  England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","Haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","lifeSummary":"Als Nicholas de Haversham II 1240 in Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war sein Vater Nicholas I Haversham 21 und seine Mutter Emma Bois 18. Er hat 1273 in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom Mrs. Joan Haversham geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1274 im Alter von 34 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1240–1274":"1240–1274","1244–1276":"1244–1276","1260–1240":"1260–1240","1273–1329":"1273–1329","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1222–Female":"1222–Desede","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1244":"1244","1276":"1276","1220":"1220","1274":"1274","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1329":"1329","Haversham, Buckinghamshire,  England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Haversham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Haversham, Buckinghamshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England"},"hu":{"1240–1274":"1240–1274","1244–1276":"1244–1276","1260–1240":"1260–1240","1273–1329":"1273–1329","1220–1255":"1220–1255","1222–Female":"1222–elhunyt","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1244":